race.comment: SKY BLUE (7) was an easy winner before the spell over shorter and looked a run short resuming in stronger than this. Will have benefited from that outing and has a handy 2kg claim. Has plenty of scope for improvement and is in the right race. TURN UP THE MUSIC (2) missed a nose over this trip and then had excuses against the above. Peaks for this and can bounce back to form. MISS DE BLAAS (4) was back to form winning this grade at Dalby from the front. Has a low barrier and the 3kg claim brings her into it. GIGGY (3) gets in light and has the rails barrier. He rates okay off the latest in better grade.
